</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C41FFC1FF08FF1FAFF8FE70" blockId="11.[151,1437,151,788]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C41FFC1FF08FF1FAD25FF0F" bold="true" box="[199,329,223,248]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" reason="1">Variations.</emphasis>
The female specimen re-described here fits very well the original description of the male, except in the following attributes: male with acrostichal setae quadriserial and 2 supra-alar setae, while the female here described the acrostichal setae are biserial and with only 1 supra-alar postsutural seta (observed through alveoli). Probably, Bezzi’s interpretation that acrostichal row is quadriserial is because they are somewhat separate, giving impression that each row is biserial and all together are quadriserial.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C3114BE55C41FFC1FF06FE54AC85FCE3" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C41FFC1FF06FE54A86BFE03" blockId="11.[151,1437,151,788]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C41FFC1FF06FE54AD56FE5B" bold="true" box="[201,314,404,428]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
The male 
<typeStatus id="54B0A6CC5C41FFC1FE7BFE54AE7AFE5B" box="[436,534,404,428]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">holotype</typeStatus>
specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F31C58FE5C41FFC1FD00FE54AF69FE5C" box="[719,773,404,427]" name="Peru" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">Peru</collectingCountry>
, Callanga was deposited in the Hungarian Natural History Museum and destroyed in 1956 when Russian artillery bombed Budapest. 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A659F5C41FFC1FC05FE77A8FFFE38" author="Bezzi, M." box="[970,1171,439,463]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" pagination="298 - 407" refId="ref9061" refString="Bezzi, M. (1909) Beitrage zur Kenntniss der sudamerikanischen Dipterenfauna auf Grund der Sammelergebnisse einer Reise in Chile, Peru und Bolivia, ausgefuhrt in den Jahren 1902 - 1904 von W. Schnuse. Fam. Empididae. Nova Acta Academiae Caesareae Leopoldino-Carolinae Germanicae Naturae Curiosorum, 91, 298 - 407." type="journal article" year="1909">Bezzi (1909: 367)</bibRefCitation>
described a conspecific female specimen from 
<collectingCountry id="F31C58FE5C41FFC1FE5CFE1CADA5FE04" box="[403,457,476,499]" name="Peru" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">Peru</collectingCountry>
, Pichisweg, and this specimen is re-described here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BB4186E5C41FFC1FF08FE3FAC85FCE3" blockId="11.[151,1437,151,788]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C41FFC1FF08FE3FAD20FDEF" box="[199,332,511,536]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" reason="1">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C41FFC1FF08FE3FAD29FDEF" bold="true" box="[199,325,511,536]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">Discussion</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
The male 
<typeStatus id="54B0A6CC5C41FFC1FE0CFE3FAE49FDE0" box="[451,549,511,535]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B63ED5C41FFC1FD85FDC0AF20FDEF" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1905" box="[586,844,512,536]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xanthocera">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C41FFC1FD85FDC0AF20FDEF" box="[586,844,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">Hilarempis xanthocera</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was originally described as dichoptic (
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C41FFC1FACEFDC0A928FDEF" box="[1281,1348,512,536]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">oculis</emphasis>
s 
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C41FFC1FA99FDC0ACDEFDCB" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">ejunctis</emphasis>
). Besides this character the thorax is dark ground-colour, antenna yellow and mesonotum with four dark bands. These characters take this species to couplet 13 of 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B63ED5C41FFC1FD02FD89A84AFDA8" authority="(Philippi, 1865)" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[717,1062,583,608]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrozona">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C41FFC1FD02FD89AF02FD97" box="[717,878,585,608]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">H. argyrozona</emphasis>
(Philippi, 1865)
</taxonomicName>
in 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A659F5C41FFC1FB85FD87A898FDA8" author="Collin, J. E." box="[1098,1268,583,607]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" refId="ref9118" refString="Collin, J. E. (1933) Empididae. Diptera of Patagonia and South Chile. Volume 4, London, British Museum of Natural History, London. Vol. 4, 334 pp., 74 figs." type="book" year="1933">Collin’s (1933)</bibRefCitation>
key. The latter species was re-described by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A659F5C41FFC1FE13FDACAE15FD73" author="Collin, J. E." box="[476,633,620,644]" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" refId="ref9118" refString="Collin, J. E. (1933) Empididae. Diptera of Patagonia and South Chile. Volume 4, London, British Museum of Natural History, London. Vol. 4, 334 pp., 74 figs." type="book" year="1933">Collin (1933)</bibRefCitation>
. Both species have cell dm slightly produced (
<figureCitation id="133004EB5C41FFC1FB42FDACA88EFD73" box="[1165,1250,620,644]" captionStart="FIGURES 70–75" captionStartId="12.[151,261,579,602]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,558]" captionTargetId="figure-502@12.[151,1436,193,558]" captionTargetPageId="12" captionText="FIGURES 70–75. Wings. 70, Hilarempis argentifera Bezzi, holotype ♀; 71, H. barbatula Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 72, H. carinata Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 73, H. elegans Bezzi, holotype ♂; 74, H. gymnaspis Bezzi, lectotype ♂ (pres. desig.); 75, H. xanthocera Bezzi, ♀ specimen from Peru." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5248054" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5248054/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">Fig. 75</figureCitation>
). They differ by ocellar setae robust (small, no longer and hardly stronger than short setae on frons in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B63ED5C41FFC1FBB5FD51A972FD5F" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[1146,1310,657,680]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrozona">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C41FFC1FBB5FD51A972FD5F" box="[1146,1310,657,680]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">H. argyrozona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), antennae entirely yellow (postpedicel black in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B63ED5C41FFC1FDF5FD75AEB0FD3B" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[570,732,693,716]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrozona">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C41FFC1FDF5FD75AEB0FD3B" box="[570,732,693,716]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">H. argyrozona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
), legs with hind femur and all tibiae dark brown (yellowish in 
<taxonomicName id="4C0B63ED5C41FFC1FF58FD19AD57FD07" baseAuthorityName="Philippi" baseAuthorityYear="1865" box="[151,315,729,752]" class="Insecta" family="Empididae" genus="Hilarempis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="67" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="argyrozona">
<emphasis id="B97FC47C5C41FFC1FF58FD19AD57FD07" box="[151,315,729,752]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="67">H. argyrozona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
). The examined specimen is female and not possible to compare with genitalia figured by 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9A659F5C41FFC1FA99FD17AC89FCE3" author="Collin, J. E." pageId="11" pageNumber="67" refId="ref9118" refString="Collin, J. E. (1933) Empididae. Diptera of Patagonia and South Chile. Volume 4, London, British Museum of Natural History, London. Vol. 4, 334 pp., 74 figs." type="book" year="1933">Collin (1933)</bibRefCitation>
.
